PARAGRAPH.#text: QEP Resources Inc. said its board has authorized the spinoff of its midstream business, QEP Field Services Co., into a stand-alone public company. The natural-gas company also unveiled a $500 million share-repurchase program. QEP said it is preparing the appropriate regulatory filings for the move but added its advisers will continue to evaluate proposals for alternate transactions for separating the midstream business. The company also said its board has named Robert F. Heinemann and Thomas C. O'Connor as directors to increase the upstream and midstream expertise on the board.
